title: Debate Erupts Over Whether New Zealand Should Join Australia As A State | 10 News
description: A debate has erupted over whether New Zealand should become the seventh state of Australia.  Kiwi political commentator David Farrar suggested the move in a recent opinion piece, saying Aotearoa needs to be “bigger to survive”.  10’s Late News explains. title: UK Council Considers Feeding Pigeons Contraceptives To Control Population | 10 News
description: A city council in the UK is considering feeding contraceptives to pigeons to control the population.   Norwich City Council previously tried tackling the problem by bringing in hawks in the hope of scaring the birds away. title: Fuel Leak Delays First Crewed Moon Mission Since Apollo Program | 10 News
description: The first crewed mission to the moon since the Apollo program has been postponed after a fuel leak was discovered in the Space Launch System rocket.  The issue was uncovered during a 49-hour launch countdown rehearsal at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida. title: Trump Administration To Withdraw 700 ICE Agents From Minnesota | 10 News
description: The Trump Administration has announced it will withdraw 700 Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) and Border Patrol agents from Minnesota.  White House border czar Tom Homan stated he was drawing down the deployment because he was seeing "unprecedented" cooperation from elected sheriffs who run county jails.  Homan said, "Let me be clear, President Trump fully intends to achieve mass deportations during this administration, and immigration enforcement actions will continue every day throughout this country."  It’s understood that around 2,000 agents will remain on the ground. title: Is Vietnam Preparing For An American War? | 10 News
description: It’s been more than 50 years since the end of Vietnam war, but leaked documents appear to reveal the country is once again preparing for an American invasion.  The 20 yearlong conflict saw more than 1.3 million people killed, with a civil conflict turbocharged by intervention from America, the Soviet Union and China.  10’s Late News explains. title: Ryan Routh Sentenced To Life In Prison For 2024 Trump Assassination Attempt | 10 News
description: Ryan Routh has been sentenced to life in prison for attempting to assassinate President Donald Trump on a Florida golf course in September 2024.  The 59-year-old was found guilty last year of five criminal counts including attempted assassination at the Trump International Golf Club in West Palm Beach after serving as his own defence lawyer at trial.  Judge Aileen Cannon said in a sentencing memorandum that Routh's crimes "undeniably warrant a life sentence".  Routh's lawyer Martin Ross said they would be appealing the case. title: Alleged Attempted Bombing Of Invasion Day Rally In Perth Declared Terror Attack | 10 News
description: The WA Premier and police have declared the alleged attempted bombing of an invasion day rally in Perth a terror attack.  A 31-year-old man is accused of throwing a home-made fragment bomb packed with ball bearings and screws into the crowd. He is now facing one additional charge of engaging in a terrorist act.
